  "prompt": "What is a Walmart Rollback? What are they for?",
  "response": "A Walmart Rollback refers to a temporary price reduction on selected items at Walmart stores or on their website. These discounts are typically designed to boost sales, clear out inventory, or offer competitive pricing to attract more customers. Rollback prices are lower than Walmart's regular prices and are often advertised prominently to encourage shoppers to take advantage of the savings while they last. This strategy helps Walmart maintain its reputation for providing low prices and good deals to consumers.",
